    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@TomAugspurger if you look at the function, _repr_html_ in core/Frame.py, you will notice that it returns hardcoded values for max-height and max-width. The display.max_columns and display.max_rows certainly allow all the columns and rows to be displayed, it just arbitrarily cuts them off with a scrollbar at 1000px and 1500px respectively. For the time being, I've just hacked at the pandas code to return max-width:none, but obviously, if I upgrade that will go away.\n\nI have changed my ipython notebook custom.css to have an infinitely resizable (in width) notebook, which I would like the pandas dataframe to follow.\n"
